This paper proposes a framework for weakly-supervised word embedding that improves performance on NLP tasks such as document classification and category representative word retrieval. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV).
